ic helper**\\\\n\\\\nI need to ensure the helper is version-agnostic, meaning no version string should be included. It shouldn’t reference library APIs directly or throw errors. I'm considering dynamic class loading after the native image build which creates a new class and launches a JVM. It’s an external process, not native, so tests under the native image may still be valid. However, testing logic outside native may not count towards native coverage, even if it compiles simply. I’ll make sure there’s no hardcoded version.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Setting up build.gradle properties**\\\\n\\\\nI need to configure the `build.gradle` properties effectively. For the `tasks.withType(Test)`, I’m considering adding a system property that sets the `proguard.gradle.test.classpath` to `sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath`. This might be allowed, and I should apply the same for `native runtimeArgs`. Additionally, can I pass `-Djava.home=${System.getenv('JAVA_HOME')}`? I wonder if `System.getProperty(\\\\\\\"java.home\\\\\\\")` will point to the GraalVM runtime inside native, but external `javac` might not be present. I'll need to verify this.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating Java methods**\\\\n\\\\nI'm reminded that using `Arrays.asList` allows null values, which is useful. I should think about the line of code stating that if the expected value doesn't equal the actual one, it throws an AssertionError - that's a clear way to signal a problem. I also note that if files are needed, ProjectBuilder might require a physical directory. It seems that temporary files can be created without cleanup, so I need to edit accordingly.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_SoTpYNuTNIy8XcPQxbNDCCQe|fc_001c9f44544a01750169fe0ce23f4081919c8d011980d0f09c\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/net.sf.proguard/proguard-gradle/5.2.1/src/test/java/net_sf_proguard/proguard_gradle/Proguard_gradleTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage net_sf_proguard.proguard_gradle;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Timeout;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\\n\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class Proguard_gradleTest {\\n    private static final String TEST_CLASSPATH_PROPERTY = \\\"proguard.gradle.test.classpath\\\";\\n    private static final String PROBE_SOURCE = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n            import org.gradle.api.Project;\\n            import org.gradle.testfixtures.ProjectBuilder;\\n            import proguard.gradle.ProGuardTask;\\n\\n            import java.io.File;\\n            import java.nio.file.Files;\\n            import java.nio.file.Path;\\n            import java.util.Arrays;\\n            import java.util.LinkedHashMap;\\n            import java.util.List;\\n            import java.util.Map;\\n\\n            public final class ProGuardTaskDslProbe {\\n                public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\\n                    final Path temporaryDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\\\"proguard-task-dsl\\\");\\n                    final Project project = ProjectBuilder.builder()\\n                            .withProjectDir(temporaryDirectory.toFile())\\n                            .build();\\n                    final ProGuardTask task = project.getTasks().create(\\\"minifyApplication\\\", ProGuardTask.class);\\n                    final File firstInputJar = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\\\"application.jar\\\").toFile();\\n                    